reviewText: Acting was unimpressive and the storyline was bad.  Language was unnecessary.  B movie at best, not recommended.

I always wonder when I see one star reviews. When it comes to Christian movies many complain about the acting, but this one featured Charlene Tilton, a seasoned and very talented actress. It seems many of the negatives are from men, and coincidentally this movie portrays at least a couple of them in a very negative light. You have to pay close attention to this movie about the filming of a documentary, as its filmed somewhat in the style of American Graffiti. I thought it was excellent, and I'm glad I watched it.

It tries to be a serious movie but the acting, writing, and plot are so terrible that I could not stop laughing throughout the movie.

It's sort-of like how Batman & Robin was hilarious.

 Amazingly low budget.
Tried sitting through this for an hour, but it was poorly written and dragged on and on. The acting was horrible.

I found this "documentary" confusing.  Actors played the family roles and much of the acting was inept.  I thought this "documentary" was going to feature real people and situations, as documentaries do.  No, this is a poorly staged fictional script.  Cannot recommend it to anyone.
I  watch more of these movies they do have a very good ending
